 is a benchmark exploration and clarification of a concept fundamental to the past, present, and future of the natural sciences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSpeciesxHistory. 0aSpeciesxPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh  aaristotle.  abiological approach.  abiological species.  abiologists.  abiology.  acontemporary definition.  adarwin.  adefinitions.  aecology.  aencyclopedic.  aepicurus.  aessentialist.  aevolution.  aevolutionary biology.  aimportant concepts.  alife sciences.  amiddle ages.  anatural history.  anatural sciences.  anonfiction.  aphilosophy and science.  aplato.  ascience history.  ascience majors.  ascientific concept.  aspecies and reproduction.  aspecies concepts.  aspecies.  asystematics.  atextbooks.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026085640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094507440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945074423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945074/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY